@node Well-formedness -- Valued Actions and Calls
@section Well-formedness -- Valued Actions and Calls

Both @code{action}s and function @code{call}s can be valued, and as such
are considered to be expressions.  The places where they can be called
are severely restricted.  The main reason is that @code{action}s and
function @code{calls} (at least the functions that contain
@code{action}s) cause a side effect.  The order of evaluation in complex
expressions becomes an issue when side effects are considered.  In order
to exclude that, valued @code{action}s and function @code{call}s can
only occur in isolation at the right hand side of an assignment or
variable definition, or (since version 2.14.0) in simple
@code{if}-expressions and @code{reply}-expressions.

An extra restriction to this rule is put on the initial value of a
global variable in a behavior.  Such an expression can not contain
@code{action}s or function @code{call}s at all, since @code{action}s are
only allowed within an @code{on}.

@menu
* Action in member variable initializer::
* Action used in a complex expression::
* Call in member variable initializer::
* Call used in a complex expression::
* Action value discarded::
* Call value discarded::
@end menu

