@node Cannot bind port to port
@subsection Cannot bind port to port

The directions of the left and right port mentioned in the binding do
not match.  The following constructs are allowed:

@itemize

@item
When binding a port of the system to a port of a component instance, the
directions must be the same:

@itemize

@item @b{provides} binds to @b{provides}
@item @b{requires} binds to @b{requires}
@end itemize

@item
When binding a port of the system to another port of the system
Component, the directions must be the opposite:

@itemize

@item @b{provides} binds to @b{requires} or vice versa.

@end itemize

@item
When binding a port of a component instance to a port of another (or the
same) component instance, the directions must be the opposite:

@itemize

@item @b{provides} binds to @b{requires} or vice versa.

@end itemize

@end itemize

@example
