@node Instance is in a cyclic binding
@subsection @code{instance} in in a cyclic binding

We can define communication ``direction'' for bindings as follows:

@itemize

@item
For two component instances communicating: the @code{requires} port directs to
the @code{provides} port in the binding.

@item
For port forwarding (an external port is forwarded to a component
instance port) or vice versa: A @code{provides} external port directs to
a component instance @code{provides} port, and a component instance
@code{requires} directs to a @code{requires} external port.

@end itemize
To prevent component re-entrancy and guarantee run-to-completion
semantics, cycles in 'directed' communication are not allowed within a
system component.

